This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a new algorithm for learning MAP parameters in Bayesian networks. It also provides theoretical insights into the algorithm, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper involves optimization problems, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the convergence behavior of the algorithm, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the information theory (cs.IT) and the social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
